      <item>
        <title>Running Drush for your Drupal Docker Containers</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;If you run sites in docroot or need to cd into a site directory in a multisite configuration. This is my prefered way&lt;br /&gt;
to quickly run drush commands unless you use a wrapper similar to bowline which is an excellent option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My sites typically include a docroot folder as is the standard with Acquia hosted sites/repos.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;c&quot;&gt;#    cmd/flag   container name        exec    wrap commands in quotes to use multi step &lt;/span&gt;
docker &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;exec&lt;/span&gt; -it drupal-container-name bash -c &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;cd /var/www/docroot &amp;amp;&amp;amp; drush uli -l drupal.loc&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
